style="border-width:0; margin-bottom:12px;"
src="https://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/4.0/88x31.png"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</copyright><lastBuildDate>Wed, 05 Jun 2024 17:13:35 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Las funciones con inversa por la izquierda son inyectivas</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/05-las_funciones_con_inversa_por_la_izquierda_son_inyectivas/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;En Lean4, que \(g\) es una inversa por la izquierda de \(f\) está definido por&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;   &lt;span class="n"&gt;LeftInverse&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;g&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;β&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;α&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;α&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;β&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kt"&gt;Prop&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;g&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;y que \(f\) tenga inversa por la izquierda está definido por&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;   &lt;span class="n"&gt;HasLeftInverse&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;α&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;β&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kt"&gt;Prop&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;finv&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;β&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;α&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;LeftInverse&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;finv&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Finalmente, que \(f\) es inyectiva está definido por&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;   &lt;span class="n"&gt;Injective&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;α&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;β&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kt"&gt;Prop&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;⦃&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;⦄,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 que si \(f\) tiene inversa por la izquierda, entonces \(f\) es inyectiva.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Tactic&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kn"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Function&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;universe&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;α&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kt"&gt;Type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;β&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kt"&gt;Type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;α&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;β&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hf&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;HasLeftInverse&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Injective&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/05-las_funciones_con_inversa_por_la_izquierda_son_inyectivas/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 3 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/05-las_funciones_con_inversa_por_la_izquierda_son_inyectivas/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 05 Jun 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>La congruencia módulo 2 es una relación de equivalencia</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/04-la_congruencia_modulo_2_es_una_relacion_de_equivalencia/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Se define la relación \(R\) entre los números enteros de forma que \(x\) está relacionado con \(y\) si \(x-y\) es divisible por 2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 que \(R\) es una relación de equivalencia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Int.Basic&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Tactic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;R&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℤ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∣&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Equivalence&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;R&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/04-la_congruencia_modulo_2_es_una_relacion_de_equivalencia/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 7 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/04-la_congruencia_modulo_2_es_una_relacion_de_equivalencia/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 04 Jun 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Si uₙ está acotada y el límite de vₙ es 0, entonces el límite de uₙ·vₙ es 0</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/03-producto_de_una_sucesion_acotada_por_otra_convergente_a_cero/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 que si \(u_n\) está acotada y el límite de \(v_n\) es \(0\), entonces el límite de \(u_n·v_n\) es \(0\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Tactic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;acotada&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hU&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;acotada&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hV&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/03-producto_de_una_sucesion_acotada_por_otra_convergente_a_cero/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 8 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/03-producto_de_una_sucesion_acotada_por_otra_convergente_a_cero/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 03 Jun 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Si (∀n)[uₙ ≤ vₙ], entonces lim uₙ ≤ lim vₙ</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/31-limite_de_sucesion_menor_que_otra_sucesion/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;En Lean4, una sucesión \(u_0, u_1, u_2, \dots\) se puede representar mediante una función \(u : ℕ → ℝ\) de forma que \(u(n)\) es el \(n\)-ésimo término de la sucesión.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Se define que \(a\) límite de la sucesión \(u\) como sigue&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;   &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="w"&gt;     &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Demostrar que si \((∀ n)[u_n ≤ v_n]\), \(a\) es límite de \(u_n\) y \(c\) es límite de \(v_n\), entonces \(a ≤ c\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hu&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hv&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;huv&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/31-limite_de_sucesion_menor_que_otra_sucesion/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 11 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/31-limite_de_sucesion_menor_que_otra_sucesion/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Si x, y ∈ ℝ tales que (∀ z)[y &lt; z → x ≤ z], entonces x ≤ y</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/30-propiedad_de_la_densidad_de_los_reales/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 que si \(x, y ∈ ℝ\) tales que \((∀ z)[y &amp;lt; z → x ≤ z]\), entonces \(x ≤ y\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;h&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;z&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;z&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;z&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/30-propiedad_de_la_densidad_de_los_reales/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 4 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/30-propiedad_de_la_densidad_de_los_reales/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 30 May 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>La paradoja del barbero</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/29-la_paradoja_del_barbero/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 la &lt;a href="https://bit.ly/3eWyvVw"&gt;paradoja del barbero&lt;/a&gt;; es decir, que no existe un hombre que afeite a todos los que no se afeitan a sí mismo y sólo a los que no se afeitan a sí mismo.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Tactic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Hombre&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kt"&gt;Type&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;afeita&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Hombre&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Hombre&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kt"&gt;Prop&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;¬&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Hombre&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Hombre&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;afeita&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;↔&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;¬&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;afeita&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/29-la_paradoja_del_barbero/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 3 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/29-la_paradoja_del_barbero/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 29 May 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Las sucesiones convergentes están acotadas</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/28-acotacion_de_convergentes/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 que si \(u_n\) es una sucesión convergente, entonces está acotada; es decir,
\[ (∃ k ∈ ℕ)(∃ b ∈ ℝ)(∀ n ∈ ℕ)[n ≥ k → |u_n| ≤ b] \]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Tactic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="c1"&gt;-- (limite u c) expresa que el límite de u es c.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="c1"&gt;-- (convergente u) expresa que u es convergente.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;convergente&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;h&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;convergente&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;b&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;b&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/28-acotacion_de_convergentes/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 4 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/28-acotacion_de_convergentes/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 28 May 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Un número es par si y solo si lo es su cuadrado</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/27-un_numero_es_par_syss_lo_es_su_cuadrado/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 que un número es par si y solo si lo es su cuadrado.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Int.Parity&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Tactic&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kn"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℤ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="n"&gt;Even&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mi"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;↔&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Even&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/27-un_numero_es_par_syss_lo_es_su_cuadrado/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 5 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/27-un_numero_es_par_syss_lo_es_su_cuadrado/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 27 May 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Los supremos de las sucesiones crecientes son sus límites</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/24-los_supremos_de_las_sucesiones_crecientes_son_sus_limites/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sea \(u\) una sucesión creciente. Demostrar con Lean4 que si \(S\) es un supremo de \(u\), entonces el límite de \(u\) es \(S\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="c1"&gt;-- (limite u c) expresa que el límite de u es c.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="c1"&gt;-- (supremo u S) expresa que el supremo de u es S.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;supremo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∧&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hu&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Monotone&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hS&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;supremo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/24-los_supremos_de_las_sucesiones_crecientes_son_sus_limites/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 7 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/24-los_supremos_de_las_sucesiones_crecientes_son_sus_limites/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 24 May 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Si `f(x) ≤ f(y) → x ≤ y`, entonces f es inyectiva</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/23-si_fx_leq_fy_to_x_leq_y_entonces_f_es_inyectiva/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 que si \(f\) una función de \(ℝ\) en \(ℝ\) tal que
\[ (∀ x, y)[f(x) ≤ f(y) → x ≤ y] \]
entonces \(f\) es inyectiva.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kn"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Function&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;h&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;},&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Injective&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/23-si_fx_leq_fy_to_x_leq_y_entonces_f_es_inyectiva/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 3 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/23-si_fx_leq_fy_to_x_leq_y_entonces_f_es_inyectiva/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 23 May 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>